{"type":"message","id":"652db0b3","parentId":"45b5a9db","timestamp":"2026-04-06T01:22:09.654Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zwenqqae66r0_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"8:const DOT_DIR = \".clawhub\";\n10:const DOT_IGNORE = \".clawhubignore\";\n81:export async function readLockfile(workdir) {\n82:    const paths = [join(workdir, DOT_DIR, \"lock.json\"), join(workdir, LEGACY_DOT_DIR, \"lock.json\")];\n95:export async function writeLockfile(workdir, lock) {\n96:    const path = join(workdir, DOT_DIR, \"lock.json\");"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":12,"aggregated":"8:const DOT_DIR = \".clawhub\";\n10:const DOT_IGNORE = \".clawhubignore\";\n81:export async function readLockfile(workdir) {\n82:    const paths = [join(workdir, DOT_DIR, \"lock.json\"), join(workdir, LEGACY_DOT_DIR, \"lock.json\")];\n95:export async function writeLockfile(workdir, lock) {\n96:    const path = join(workdir, DOT_DIR, \"lock.json\");","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775438529648}}
{"type":"message","id":"552c020d","parentId":"652db0b3","timestamp":"2026-04-06T01:22:21.216Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the lockfile is at `<workdir>/.clawhub/lock.json`. The default workdir is `cwd` (current working directory). So when you run `clawhub install foo`, it installs to `<cwd>/skills/foo`.\n\nNow I understand the situation better. Let me just answer the user's questions directly:\n\n1. Are skills stored in OpenViking? \n   - The clawhub registry is pointing to mirror-cn.clawhub.com (China mirror) ✓\n   - But the actual skill files are installed relative to `cwd` (by default `~/.openclaw/workspace`)\n   - The `clawhub list` shows skills because it reads from the lockfile at `~/.openclaw/workspace/.clawhub/lock.json`\n\n2. Does the user need to reinstall?\n   - If OpenViking uses a different workspace directory, then yes, skills would need to be reinstalled there\n   - Let me check what OpenViking uses as its workspace\n\nActually wait - the user said they switched memory system to openviking. This doesn't necessarily mean the workspace directory changed. But the skills (like feishu-*) were installed in `~/.openclaw/extensions/openclaw-lark/skills/` which is an OpenClaw-specific path. OpenViking might use a different structure.\n\nLet me just give a clear answer based on what I found.","thinkingSignature":"cb88d668c01292a80e8e0fa24771dcbe71e3a6bd3ebe5f1a060f3caa521a4eb0"},{"type":"text","text":"根据检查结果：\n\n**1. 源已切换国内** ✓\n```\n~/.config/clawhub/config.json → registry: https://mirror-cn.clawhub.com\n```\n\n**2. Skills 存储位置**\n\n| 路径 | 说明 |\n|------|------|\n| `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/` | OpenClaw workspace skills |\n| `~/.openclaw/extensions/openclaw-lark/skills/` | 飞书官方 skills |\n| `~/.openclaw/skills/` | OpenClaw 全局 skills |\n| `~/.openviking/viking/` | OpenViking 数据目录 |\n\n**3. 是否需要重新安装？**\n\n`clawhub list` 显示的那些 skills 记录在 `~/.openclaw/workspace/.clawhub/lock.json`，但 OpenViking 使用独立的数据结构（`~/.openviking/`）。\n\n**结论**：如果 OpenViking 有独立的 workspace 或 skills 目录——是的，需要在 OpenViking 对应路径下重新安装。原来的 skills 在 `~/.openclaw/` 下，OpenViking 看不到。\n\n你想让我帮你查一下 OpenViking 的实际 skills 存放路径吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":8600,"output":519,"cacheRead":12509,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21628,"cost":{"input":0.00258,"output":0.0006228,"cacheRead":0.00075054,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00395334}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775438529655,"responseId":"06223dc184117b09396d86101e33f5f3"}}
{"type":"message","id":"51860918","parentId":"552c020d","timestamp":"2026-04-06T01:26:49.888Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"openclaw-weixin:1775438742534-31247d57\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-04-06 09:25 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\n简单一句。想让你后面能正常的使用skill 主目录下的skill全部删除，重新通过clawhub install 安装。完成完成后默认就回存在openViking中对吗"}],"timestamp":1775438809759}}
{"type":"message","id":"98beed5d","parentId":"51860918","timestamp":"2026-04-06T01:27:09.169Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to:\n1. Delete all skills in the OpenClaw workspace/skills directory\n2. Reinstall them via clawhub install\n3. Expect that after reinstalling, they will be in OpenViking's directory automatically\n\nLet me check - the clawhub install command installs to the current working directory's `skills` subfolder by default. So if I run `clawhub install xxx` from the OpenViking workspace, it should install there.\n\nBut first, I need to understand what the OpenViking workspace is. The user seems to assume that after reinstalling via clawhub, skills will end up in OpenViking. This depends on:\n1. What directory clawhub installs to (defaults to cwd, which is the workspace directory)\n2. Whether the current working directory is set to OpenViking's workspace\n\nLet me just do what the user asked - delete the old skills and reinstall them. But I should be careful and ask for confirmation before deleting.\n\nActually the user asked simply \"简单一句\" - meaning they want a simple answer. They asked if after reinstalling via clawhub, skills will automatically be in OpenViking.\n\nThe answer is: it depends on where you run clawhub install from. If you run it from the OpenViking workspace directory, yes. Otherwise no.\n\nBut wait - let me think about this differently. The user might be saying \"后续能正常使用 skill\" - meaning \"for you to be able to use skills normally afterwards\". The skills I have access to are defined in the available_skills section at startup. These are loaded from specific paths.\n\nLooking at the system prompt, it shows skills at paths like:\n- `~/.openclaw/extensions/openclaw-lark/skills/feishu-bitable/SKILL.md`\n- `~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/clawflow/SKILL.md`\n- `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/clawhub/SKILL.md`\n\n\n- `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/clawhub/SKILL.md`\n\nSo the skills shown in the system are loaded from specific paths. The OpenViking skills must be in a separate location. If the user reinstalls skills in the OpenViking workspace directory, those new installations would be accessible to OpenViking but my system prompt wouldn't automatically see them unless they're in the paths I'm configured to load from. The user needs to either ensure clawhub installs to the paths I actually read from, or the OpenViking system needs to share the same skills directory as my configured paths. The user's assumption isn't quite right. Skills installed via clawhub go to whichever directory I run the command from, not automatically to OpenViking. I should verify the OpenViking workspace path first, then delete the old OpenClaw skills and reinstall them in the correct location so they're actually accessible.","thinkingSignature":"1f4532f81c08fe54cf6eeef4fe358b1227a1275bf2225a737159a8a42177f8f2"},{"type":"text","text":"不一定。clawhub 默认安装到**当前工作目录**（cwd）下的 `skills/` 子目录。\n\n如果从 `~/.openclaw/workspace` 安装 → 还在 OpenClaw 路径\n如果从 OpenViking workspace 安装 → 才会进 OpenViking\n\n先确认一下 OpenViking 的 workspace 在哪：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ycjapuctmjiy_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"OpenClaw workspace: ~/.openclaw/workspace\" && ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/ && echo \"---\" && cat ~/.openviking/ov.conf | grep -A2 workspace"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":39,"output":715,"cacheRead":12509,"cacheWrite":7686,"totalTokens":20949,"cost":{"input":0.0000117,"output":0.0008579999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00075054,"cacheWrite":0.0028822500000000003,"total":0.00450249}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775438809766,"responseId":"06223edab388cf6034cfb40a1c89805b"}}
