{"type":"message","id":"a14d30c5","parentId":"94a5179c","timestamp":"2026-04-06T01:27:17.893Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The OpenViking config says workspace is `/data` but that directory doesn't seem to exist. The actual OpenViking data is in `~/.openviking/`. The workspace skills that clawhub list shows might actually be in the OpenClaw workspace since that's where I was running from.\n\nLet me think about this more carefully. When the user runs `clawhub list`, it shows:\n```\nself-improving-agent  3.0.6\nskill-vetter  1.0.0\n...\n```\n\nThese are being listed because they're in the current working directory's `.clawhub/lock.json` or similar. My cwd is `~/.openclaw/workspace/`.\n\nActually wait - I need to re-examine. The clawhub CLI has a `--workdir` and `--dir` option. By default it uses cwd. So if I'm in `~/.openclaw/workspace/`, then `clawhub install xxx` would install to `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/xxx`.\n\nBut the user wants skills to go to OpenViking. OpenViking's workspace is configured as `/data` which doesn't exist. So maybe the skills need to go to a different path.\n\nActually, maybe I should just ask the user - where is the OpenViking workspace? Or does OpenViking use `~/.openviking/` as its workspace directory?\n\nLet me check what's in the OpenViking default agent directory more thoroughly.","thinkingSignature":"2a33a5707c5d15332e604210c9d05caf2944976aab12dbb17b5583908a7b4054"},{"type":"text","text":"\nOpenViking 配置的 workspace 是 `/data`，但这个目录不存在。OpenViking 实际数据在 `~/.openviking/`。\n\n**你的 OpenViking workspace 具体在哪个路径？** 我确认一下，然后才能正确删除和重装。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":8527,"output":348,"cacheRead":12509,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21384,"cost":{"input":0.0025581,"output":0.00041759999999999996,"cacheRead":0.00075054,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0037262399999999996}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775438829218,"responseId":"06223eed85bd392492db1